For a gimmick as simple as this, it's very easy to it to fall into the territory of becoming annoying to read. This falls into that trap right when the anomaly starts talking about its past. While a demon being hunted down by other demons for some mistake it made in Hell is not exactly the most interesting of backstories, the way that it's told makes it even more mind-numbing to read and digest. If the narrative was reworked to focus more on the comedic aspects of the bird  I think I would've had myself a few immature chuckles and liked it a lot more. As is, it's just a boring story told in a gimmicky way.

This is a -1 from me.







